.SH NAME
HTMLElement.lang \- HTMLElement: lang property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]HTMLElement.lang\f[B]\f[R] property gets or sets the base
language of an element\[cq]s attribute values and text content.
.PP
The language code returned by this property is defined in RFC 5646: Tags
for Identifying Languages (also known as BCP 47).
Common examples include \[lq]en\[rq] for English, \[lq]ja\[rq] for
Japanese, \[lq]es\[rq] for Spanish and so on.
The default value of this attribute is \f[CR]unknown\f[R].
Note that this attribute, though valid at the individual element level
described here, is most often specified for the root element of the
document.
.PP
This also only works with the \f[CR]lang\f[R] attribute and not with
\f[CR]xml:lang\f[R].
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// this snippet compares the base language and\f[R]
\f[I]// redirects to another URL based on language\f[R]
\f[B]if\f[R] (document.documentElement.lang === \[dq]en\[dq]) {
  window.location.href = \[dq]Some_document.html.en\[dq];
} \f[B]else\f[R] \f[B]if\f[R] (document.documentElement.lang === \[dq]ru\[dq]) {
  window.location.href = \[dq]Some_document.html.ru\[dq];
}
